commText: Rahane and Gaikwad are at the crease. Rahane is on strike. Bhuvneshwar will open the attack
Bhuvneshwar to Rahane, 2 runs, length delivery on middle, tucked away to deep square leg, they get back for a couple. No real swing there
Bhuvneshwar to Rahane, no run, length delivery on middle, Rahane bunts it towards cover watchfully
Bhuvneshwar to Rahane, no run, length delivery outside off, just a hint of shape away and Rahane had a waft at this before getting beaten
Bhuvneshwar to Rahane, no run, good length delivery on off-stump, Rahane takes a couple of steps down the wicket before blocking it solidly into the off-side
Bhuvneshwar to Rahane, 1 run, length delivery on middle, tucked away to deep square leg
Bhuvneshwar to Gaikwad, 1 run, length delivery on off-stump, eased towards point for a quick single, tidy start from Bhuvneshwar
Nitish Reddy, right-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
Nitish Reddy to Gaikwad, wide, length delivery that's pushed down leg, false start
Nitish Reddy to Gaikwad, 1 run, good length delivery on off-stump, Gaikwad hangs back and eases it towards backward point for one

Nitish Reddy to Rahane, 1 run, length delivery just outside off, Rahane hangs back to defend and gets a thick inside edge onto the pads, it dribbles into the off-side and they scamper through for a single
Nitish Reddy to Gaikwad, 1 run, length delivery on middle, bunted towards mid-wicket for one
SRH review. There was a wide signalled as this went down leg and Klaasen was appealing politely for a caught behind, looks like the review is for the wide

Nitish Reddy to Rahane, no run, review successful, short of length and just angling down leg, Rahane looked to help it fine with a pull and missed, just brushed a bit of his shirt on its way through to Klaasen so the wide will be overturned
Nitish Reddy to Rahane, leg byes, 1 run, good length delivery on middle-leg, Rahane looks to tuck it into the leg-side and it hits his thigh pad, they pinch a leg-bye as it goes towards square leg
Nitish Reddy to Gaikwad, FOUR, that will be the first boundary! Just short of length on off-stump, Gaikwad hung back and was waiting for it, he pulled it away over mid-wicket and it raced away
Rahane vs Bhuvneshwar in IPL (before today) Runs: 96 Balls: 108 Dismissals: 6 Avg: 16.0 SR: 88.88
Bhuvneshwar to Rahane, FOUR, nicely played! Length delivery on off-stump, Rahane shuffled forward and across and used the pace to pull it away to deep backward square leg
Bhuvneshwar to Rahane, 1 run, length delivery outside off, punched towards cover for a quick single
Bhuvneshwar to Gaikwad, 1 run, good length delivery on off-stump, Gaikwad eases it towards cover for a quick single
Bhuvneshwar to Rahane, no run, length delivery outside off, slapped straight to cover
Bhuvneshwar to Rahane, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Bhuvneshwar to Rahane, out Caught by Shahbaz Ahmed!! In the air and straight to the man! Length delivery just outside off, Rahane looked to loft this through the line and over mid-on, wasn't full enough for that but he went through with his shot anyway. Ended up being a bit of a nothing shot as it shot straight up in the air before going down to the man at deep mid-wicket. Simple catch and Rahane walks back. This has been a slow start for CSK! Rahane c Shahbaz Ahmed b Bhuvneshwar 9(12) [4s-1]
Rahane vs Bhuvneshwar in IPL Runs: 104 Balls: 117 Dismissals: 7 Avg: 14.85 SR: 88.88
Ajinkya Rahane vs Pacers this IPL Inns: 8 Runs: 129 Balls: 96 Dismissals: 6 Avg: 21.5 SR: 134.4
Daryl Mitchell, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Bhuvneshwar to Mitchell, no run, length delivery just outside off, blocked towards cover
CSK opening partnership this IPL Inns: 9 Runs: 190 Avg: 21.11 RR: 8.08 50+: 1 - CSK's opening stand aggregate runs, average, RR and 50+ stand are the lowest among all teams.
Shahbaz Ahmed, Left arm orthodox, comes into the attack
Shahbaz Ahmed to Gaikwad, no run, full on off-stump, Ruturaj makes room to drive but mistimes it back to the bowler
Shahbaz Ahmed to Gaikwad, 1 run, full just outside off, Gaikwad makes room and drives it out towards cover
Shahbaz Ahmed to Mitchell, 1 run, full just outside off, knocked towards cover
Shahbaz Ahmed to Gaikwad, FOUR, nicely played! Length delivery just outside off, Gaikwad presses back and across, just creates enough width and cuts it away sharply through to the deep point fence
Shahbaz Ahmed to Gaikwad, FOUR, lovely use of the crease again! Tossed up full on middle, Gaikwad backs away to make room and creams the drive to the deep extra cover fence
Shahbaz Ahmed to Gaikwad, 1 run, full on off-stump, driven out to deep extra cover again, protection there this time
Bhuvneshwar to Gaikwad, 1 run, good length delivery on off-stump, Gaikwad hangs back and eases it towards backward point
Slip in place
Bhuvneshwar to Mitchell, FOUR, clean strike! Pitched up full on middle, Mitchell stood still and just lofted this straight back over the bowler, held his shape nicely and timed it to perfection
Bhuvneshwar to Mitchell, 1 run, length delivery on middle, tucked away to deep square leg

Bhuvneshwar to Gaikwad, FOUR, beautiful shot! Length delivery just outside off, nothing wrong with this delivery, Gaikwad hung back and waited for it before opening the face of the bat to cut it to the right of the man at backward point, superb placement

Bhuvneshwar to Gaikwad, FOUR, glorious! Fuller and wider outside off, Gaikwad leans into a cover drive and it rockets away to the ropes, man at deep point sprinted and dived to his right but couldn't stop it
Lowest average at Chennai in IPL (min 150+ balls faced) 14.80 - Ajinkya Rahane* 18.65 - Ravindra Jadeja 19.10 - Mayank Agarwal 19.30 - Wriddhiman Saha
Bhuvneshwar to Gaikwad, 1 run, good length delivery on off-stump, eased towards point for one, 15 off that over, CSK needed that
Natarajan to start round the wicket to the right hander
T Natarajan, left-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
T Natarajan to Gaikwad, no run, very full on off-stump, almost yorker length and Gaikwad knocks it back to the bowler

T Natarajan to Gaikwad, FOUR, too straight and punished! Length delivery angling into the pads, Gaikwad stood still and just helped it on its way with a pull, beat short fine-leg to his left and raced away
T Natarajan to Gaikwad, 1 run, good length delivery on off-stump, eased towards point for one
T Natarajan to Mitchell, no run, full on off-stump, Mitchell pushed it straight back towards the bowler who got a hand on it, Mitchell wanted a single as it went towards mid-off but he was sent back
T Natarajan to Mitchell, no run, length delivery on off-stump, tucked straight to mid-wicket
T Natarajan to Mitchell, no run, fires in a perfect yorker on middle, all Mitchell can do is block it out, good finish to the over

Powerplay summary -- Gaikwad gets CSK going after slow start -- Superb start from Bhuvi who is accurate as ever -- Bhuvi gets rid of Rahane for 9 (2.5) -- Seventh time he's got him in IPL -- Shahbaz goes for 11 in his first over -- Bhuvi goes for 15 in his third over -- Tight over from Natarajan to finish the powerplay
Jaydev Unadkat, left-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
Unadkat to Gaikwad, 1 run, length delivery outside off, Unadkat bowling round the wicket too, Gaikwad eases it down to third man
Unadkat to Mitchell, FOUR, nicely struck! Touch too full outside off, Mitchell smacked it through extra cover, was struck on the up and right into the gap
Unadkat to Mitchell, 1 run, full just outside off, knocked straight to mid-off for a quick single
Unadkat to Gaikwad, 2 runs, banged in short on middle, Gaikwad plays a controlled pull down to deep square leg, slight fumble and they get back for two easily
Unadkat to Gaikwad, 1 run, length delivery on off-stump, punched out towards deep point
Unadkat to Mitchell, no run, full and just outside off, knocked straight to cover
Shahbaz Ahmed [1.0-0-11-0] is back into the attack
Shahbaz Ahmed to Gaikwad, no run, full just outside off, Gaikwad comes down the track and drives it straight to extra cover
Shahbaz Ahmed to Gaikwad, 2 runs, flatter delivery just outside off, Gaikwad presses back and cuts it away to deep backward point, they get a couple as it was away to the fielder's left
Not sure what the delay is about, the CSK physio is out there. Looks like the heat is taking a toll on the players
Shahbaz Ahmed to Gaikwad, no run, flatter delivery just outside off, Gaikwad presses back and mistimes a cut towards backward point, that seemed to hold up a bit

Shahbaz Ahmed to Gaikwad, FOUR, struck into the gap! Flatter delivery outside off, Gaikwad presses back and cuts it away sharply again, made enough room and put it far enough away to the left of the man at deep point
Shahbaz Ahmed to Gaikwad, 1 run, full on off-stump, pushed down the ground to long off
Shahbaz Ahmed to Mitchell, 1 run, full on off-stump, Mitchell presses forward and knocks it down the ground to long-off
Pat Cummins, right-arm fast, comes into the attack

Cummins to Mitchell, SIX, beautiful shot! Full and just outside off, Mitchell just lofted straight through the line and over long-off, impeccable timing and it sailed over, 50-run stand comes up as well
Cummins to Mitchell, no run, length delivery on off-stump, bunted into the leg-side towards mid-on
Cummins to Mitchell, 1 run, good length delivery on off-stump, mistimed heave goes down towards long-on off the toe end
Cummins to Gaikwad, 1 run, length delivery just outside off, punched down towards sweeper cover
Cummins to Mitchell, 1 run, good length delivery on off-stump, punched down to long-on
Cummins to Gaikwad, SIX, CRUNCHED! That's a nice way to bring up fifty! Just short of length on off-stump, Gaikwad hung back and played a cracking pull shot to send it sailing over deep mid-wicket

Timeout. CSK have been relatively circumspect but they've kept the boundaries coming. Ruturaj looks to be in full flow today as well and he's backed up his 100 in the last game with a 50 today. They've only lost one wicket so expect them to start going a little harder hereafter
Jaydev Unadkat [1.0-0-9-0] is back into the attack
Unadkat to Mitchell, 1 run, slower short ball on off-stump, gets up fairly high and Mitchell mistimes a pull down towards square leg
Unadkat to Gaikwad, 1 run, slower short ball on middle, Gaikwad makes some room and delays his shot as he eases it towards short third man for a quick single
SRH's spinners has conceded at ER of 11.79 before this game, which is the highest for any team this IPL

Unadkat to Mitchell, FOUR, in the slot and he pays the price! Full on off-stump, right in the slot for Mitchell and he drills it straight back over the bowler's head with disdain, that went to the ropes very quickly
Unadkat to Mitchell, 1 run, length delivery on off-stump, pushed towards mid-on for one

Unadkat to Gaikwad, 2 runs, good work in the deep, length delivery on middle, Gaikwad pressed right back and pulled it away uppishly into the gap at deep backward square leg, Nitish Reddy the fielder, covered good ground to his right and pushed it back in to keep it down to two
Unadkat to Gaikwad, 1 run, slower short ball just outside off, pulled away towards deep square leg, no real timing on this
T Natarajan [1.0-0-5-0] is back into the attack
T Natarajan to Gaikwad, no run, length delivery just outside off, Gaikwad stays leg-side and slaps it straight to cover
T Natarajan to Gaikwad, wide, banged in too short outside off, sailed well over his head
T Natarajan to Gaikwad, 1 run, full and into the pads, flicked away to deep mid-wicket
T Natarajan to Mitchell, 1 run, very full on off-stump, doesn't allow the batter to get under that, Mitchell pushes it down to long-on
T Natarajan to Gaikwad, 1 run, full and angling into off-stump, flicked away to deep mid-wicket

T Natarajan to Mitchell, FOUR, that's well played! Back of a length and outside off, must have been pace off too and Mitchell sliced it up and over third short third man, he had to really reach out for that
T Natarajan to Mitchell, 1 run, full on off-stump, driven down to long-off
Shahbaz Ahmed [2.0-0-19-0] is back into the attack
Shahbaz Ahmed to Mitchell, FOUR, too straight and it races away! Flatter delivery drifting on to the pads, Mitchell leant in and just paddled it very fine, no chance for the man at short fine-leg
Shahbaz Ahmed to Mitchell, FOUR, superb batting! Full on middle, Mitchell made room very early before lofting it straight back over the bowler's head, split long-on and long-off to perfection
Long-off moves very straight
Shahbaz Ahmed to Mitchell, 1 run, full on middle-leg, looked to go big and loft it down the ground again, didn't time it this time and it goes towards wide long-on
Shahbaz Ahmed to Gaikwad, 1 run, length delivery just outside off, pushed down to long-off

Shahbaz Ahmed to Mitchell, 2 runs, length delivery on the pads, Mitchell pressed back and whipped it away into the gap at cow corner, two men converged and managed to keep it in betwen them, was timed very sweetly
Looks like Shahbaz Ahmed is already struggling to grip the ball, seems to be plenty of dew setting in already

Shahbaz Ahmed to Mitchell, 2 runs, length delivery full and just outside off, Mitchell looks to loft it over extra cover but doesn't time it at all, goes over the circle and lands well short of the man running in from the deep
Pat Cummins [1.0-0-15-0] is back into the attack
Cummins to Gaikwad, 1 run, full and just outside off, swiped away to deep square leg
Cummins to Mitchell, no run, full and into the pads, Mitchell missed out there, he was looking to flick it away and got a thick inside edge onto the pads
Cummins to Mitchell, FOUR, very clever batting! That's the 100-run stand as well, full and very wide outside off, Mitchell shuffled all the way across and scooped it over short third man's head
Second 100+ partnership for CSK this season after 104 by Gaikwad & Dube against LSG in the last match.
Cummins to Mitchell, 1 run, that's 50 for Mitchell, short of length on off-stump, pulled away to deep square leg
First 50+ score for Daryl Mitchell in IPL
Cummins to Gaikwad, 1 run, full on leg-stump, Gaikwad made some room and shoveled it out towards long-off, fielder takes it on the bounce
Cummins to Mitchell, 1 run, length delivery outside off, Mitchell flat-bats it down the ground to long-on, only one

Timeout. Both these batters are going along very nicely now. Mitchell has done the bulk of the scoring of late and has gotten to his fifty as well - his first in the IPL. They've got a great platform to expand upon now.
Jaydev Unadkat [2.0-0-19-0] is back into the attack
Unadkat to Mitchell, 1 run, full on the stumps, Mitchell drives to deep mid-wicket
Unadkat to Gaikwad, wide, Gaikwad makes room outside the leg-stump and Unadkat bowls a slower ball full outside off, outside the tramline
Unadkat to Gaikwad, 1 run, fine yorker length delivery on off, Gaikwad shimmies around and then digs it wide of backward point
Unadkat to Mitchell, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Unadkat to Mitchell, out Caught by Nitish Reddy!! Straight to deep mid-wicket. A low full-toss on the stumps, Mitchell slugs it and finds deep mid-wicket. They are now checking for the height on this. Mitchell has been asked to wait. And he has been given out as the umps have a word with him. The partnership is broken. Mitchell c Nitish Reddy b Unadkat 52(32) [4s-7 6s-1]

Unadkat to Gaikwad, 1 run, fullish outside off, Gaikwad drags the heave to long-on

Highlights (Overs 7-14) -- 84/1, 10.5rpo -- Mitchell raises tempo after slow start -- From 12 off 11 balls, he raises fifty in 29 balls -- Cummins goes for 15 in his first over -- Gaikwad brings up fifty off 27 balls (8.6) -- Unadkat removes Mitchell for 52 (13.3)

Bhuvneshwar to Gaikwad, SIX, smashed over deep mid-wicket. A short delivery at Gaikwad who stands tall and pulls meatily into the stands, was the slower short ball too

Cummins to Shivam Dube, 1 run, slower ball off-cutter outside off, Shivam Dube cuts to deep extra-cover
Cummins to Gaikwad, FOUR, superb from Gaikwad. A low full-toss outside off, Gaikwad reaches for it and opens the face of the bat to slice it between backward point and short third man
Cummins to Gaikwad, FOUR, slower ball off-cutter down leg, Gaikwad swivels to pull and gets it wide of Natarajan at fine-leg who was running to his right, one bounce over the ropes

T Natarajan to Shivam Dube, SIX, T Natarajan misses the yorker length and Shivam Dube puts him away. A half-volley on the stumps, Shivam Dube clears his front leg and heaves over deep mid-wicket, just cleared the man
Shivam Dube reviews for a non-wide.
T Natarajan to Shivam Dube, wide, slower ball off-cutter down leg, Shivam Dube pulls and misses, just wide and it's been called a wide. Cummins can only smile wryly. The review works for Dube

T Natarajan to Shivam Dube, 1 run, great attempt at a caught and bowled. Natarajan runs forward and dives, gets a hand on it, but fails to hang on. Full and at the pads, Shivam Dube heaves and the thick inside-edge onto the pads lobs up, Natarajan did so well but failed to take it
Natarajan round the wicket now.
T Natarajan to Gaikwad, 1 run, yorker length outside off, Gaikwad paddles it to fine-leg
T Natarajan to Shivam Dube, SIX, that's the power of Shivam Dube. A low full-toss outside off, he gets forward and lofts with an open face, flies over deep extra-cover. Went 80m
T Natarajan to Shivam Dube, wide, misses the yorker as Shivam Dube gets inside the line to leave this low full-toss down leg, another wide
T Natarajan to Shivam Dube, 1 run, slower short ball at Shivam Dube who makes room outside the leg-stump, pulled to fine-leg
Cummins to Shivam Dube, SIX, smashed. A wide slower ball off-cutter outside off on a good length, Shivam Dube gets across and pummels it straight down the ground. Unreal power
Cummins to Shivam Dube, wide, loopy slower short ball dug in outside off, but too high and too wide, left alone to take the wide
Cummins to Shivam Dube, FOUR, seam-up and full on the stumps, Shivam Dube clears his front leg and heaves, wide of long-on and the fielder running around can't cut it off
Cummins to Shivam Dube, byes, 1 run, slower short ball outside off, Shivam Dube slashes and misses, Klaasen can't handle it on the bounce, gives away a bye
Cummins to Gaikwad, 1 run, slower off-cutter on a good length outside off, pulled to deep mid-wicket
Cummins to Shivam Dube, 1 run, full seam-up outside off, Shivam Dube drills the drive to deep extra-cover
Cummins to Gaikwad, 2 runs, slower ball off-cutter full outside off, Gaikwad toe-ends the loft and just clears extra-cover running back
Jaydev Unadkat [3.0-0-30-1] is back into the attack
Unadkat to Shivam Dube, 2 runs, slower ball off-cutter dug in, Shivam Dube pulls wide of deep mid-wicket and with those long strides gets back for two
Unadkat to Shivam Dube, 1 run, slower short ball again, at Shivam Dube who can only find deep backward square leg with the pull
Unadkat to Gaikwad, 2 runs, slower and on a good length outside off, Gaikwad lofts wide of deep extra-cover for two more

Unadkat to Gaikwad, 2 runs, Cummins had he sent a better throw, Gaikwad was gone. A slower ball off-cutter outside off, cut to point and Cummins threw it hard and wide of the stumps and the bowler couldn't get across in time, Gaikwad had given up by then, no backing up and they take one more
Unadkat to Gaikwad, 1 run, slower ball off-cutter full outside off, Gaikwad mistimes the drive to long-off
Unadkat to Shivam Dube, no run, great over this for SRH. Just 8 off it. A slower ball off-cutter full outside off, drilled to mid-off and it's a dot
T Natarajan [3.0-0-31-0] is back into the attack
T Natarajan to Gaikwad, no run, slower ball down leg, Gaikwad can only glove it on the bounce to Klaasen, another dot
T Natarajan to Gaikwad, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

T Natarajan to Gaikwad, out Caught by Nitish Reddy!! Gaikwad falls for 98. A slower ball full on the stumps, Gaikwad does not get under it for the loft, miscues it and it's down deep mid-wicket's throat. Nitish makes no mistake. Gaikwad shakes his head as he walks back for 98. Fine innings nonetheless. Gaikwad c Nitish Reddy b T Natarajan 98(54) [4s-10 6s-3]

And guess who has come out for the crowd to lose their minds. MSD. Yet another night that most people won't ever forget. You have to hear the noise to believe it. Yellow flags being waved. Whistles being tooted. Shouting, screeching and what not! I0$ Forcing them to switch off their brains till he is there.
MS Dhoni, right handed bat, comes to the crease
First time a batter got out in nineties this season

T Natarajan to Dhoni, FOUR, was half a chance at deep square leg and credit to the fielder who went for it. A low full-toss on the stumps, flicked in the air and Abhishek was the man, dives forward but the ball bounces just in front of the right hand and goes under it, runs away for four and again the crowd go bonkers
T Natarajan to Dhoni, 1 run, slower ball off-cutter outside off, Dhoni mistimes the pull to deep square leg
T Natarajan to Shivam Dube, SIX, low full-toss on the stumps, flicked and it's high and handsome over deep mid-wicket, flies away. Crucial six for CSK
T Natarajan to Shivam Dube, 1 run, a low full-toss outside off, Shivam Dube swings hard and the thick outside-edge is on the bounce, short third man dives to his right and stops it. CSK end at 212

21:25 Local Time, 15:55 GMT, 21:25 IST: CSK once again go past 200. Last game here against LSG they made 210 and lost. Tonight they have got 212, will that be enough? Coming back to this innings, it was again the Gaikwad show with contributions from Mitchell and Shivam Dube. Rahane fell early but Gaikwad and Mitchell strung together a 107-run stand. Mitchell who hasn't fired at all this season made a timely return to form with his first fifty in the IPL. But it was the CSK skipper though who was the star. Yet another attractive innings and he looked set for consecutive tons till the heat and humidity of Chennai sapped all his energy and by the end of his knock, he was visibly tired and his dismissal was a tired shot. Dube did his job and once again MS did what he does always - come out to milk the crowd and give them what they want - despite facing just 2 balls. Excellent last two overs for SRH as only 20 came off it. Will that be the difference? Let's find out when we are back for the chase in 5 minutes...

Mitchell: We'll take that score. There's a little bit of dew around and we'll have to bowl well. Back ourselves to get the job done. It was about trying to keep putting pressure. Knew the pitch would be slightly slow. It's a new wicket. We'll throw ourselves around (on the field) and try to get the job done. He's a beautiful player to watch (Gaikwad).
Welcome back. CSK have their impact player - Shardul Thakur in. Dube out. Chahar with a wide slip.
